NORMALISED EXTRACT:
Rules (exact): For each integer i from 1 to n inclusive produce an output value as follows: if (i % 3 === 0 and i % 5 === 0) output "FizzBuzz"; else if (i % 3 === 0) output "Fizz"; else if (i % 5 === 0) output "Buzz"; else output i (the integer). The check for divisibility-by-both must occur before the single checks (equivalently, check i % 15 === 0 first).

